{"home":{"description":"For quite some time now, I've been deeply passionate about color grading, cinematography, and software development; this website is designed to showcase the various projects I’ve worked on in these three fields. \n\nWhen I was 8, I realized that I could share the stories I made up with my toy cars, simply by taking thousands of pictures of them and editing them together on the family computer. This interest in stop-motion slowly progressed into a more general interest in content creation and filmmaking, which I've now narrowed down to cinematography and color grading — although I still very much enjoy other aspects of this process, such as editing, visual effects, sound editing, etc...\n\nIn parallel, I discovered programming, which not only supported my interest in filmmaking by letting me develop [specialized tools](/work/software/metacoloreditor), but also tell its own stories, through web development, for example.\n\n\nThese disciplines all require a blend of creative and technical skills, each complementing the other, which is perhaps what I enjoy most about them: the magic of mastering a technical skill in order to translate an idea into reality never wears off, and pushes me to always continue learning about and exploring these fields","metadescription":"For quite some time now, I've been deeply passionate about color grading, cinematography, and software development; this website serves to showcase the various projects I've had the chance to work on, in all three of these fields.","metaimage":{"url":"/uploads/home_fa109d65dc.jpg"},"subtitle":"Cinematography • Color grading • Software development","underconstruction":null,"images":[{"document":{"tags":[{"name":"Color Grading","icon":"<svg version=\"1.1\" id=\"Layer_1\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" xmlns:xlink=\"http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink\" x=\"0px\" y=\"0px\" \t viewBox=\"0 0 14 12.5\" style=\"enable-background:new 0 0 14 12.5;\" xml:space=\"preserve\"> <path d=\"M7,1c3.4,0,6